#1: 🎧 Case Study: Musikko — Redefining Free Music Streaming
1. 🔍 Project Overview
Project Name: Musikko
Type: UI/UX Design for a Music Streaming App
Goal: To design a visually appealing, user-friendly app that balances ad-free music for all with sustainable monetization and optional premium features.
2. 🧠 Problem Statement
"How can we design a music app that provides a premium-feeling experience to free users without annoying interruptions, while still allowing room for monetization?"
3. 🎯 Goals & Requirements
Clean, bold visual identity
Discoverable playlists and genres
A smooth onboarding and browsing experience
Limited ad integration without interrupting playback
Scalability for future premium add-ons
4. 🖌️ Branding & Visual Direction
Logo: Waveform + Headphones icon
Color Scheme: Gold/Yellow + Black (bold, youthful, premium)

5. 🧩 Wireframes / Low-Fidelity Designs
Show sketches or grayscale layouts of Home, Search, Playlist, Player screens.
6. 🖼️ Final UI Screens
Splash Screen with Logo
Home Screen with Continue Listening + Playlists
Search Screen with genre cards and trending searches
Playlist View
(Optional) Mini Player / Now Playing
💡 Add a screen recording or mock interaction if possible.
7. 📈 Monetization Strategy
Intro video ads on app open only (skippable after 5 sec), minimal banner ads, premium features like offline mode or artist exclusives planned.
This shows business thinking behind the design.
8. 🔮 Future Enhancements
Add animations (waveform pulse, transitions)
Social listening / friend activity
Artist pages & discovery algorithms
Light/dark mode toggle
9. 🙌 Learnings & Reflections
User flow planning helped shape better features
Spacing and visual hierarchy improved readability
Designing for free users required creative thinking in monetization